	<li><a href="steig/contents.html">Michael Steig's <span class="book">Dickens and 
	Phiz</span></a> (1978)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Works by Charles Dickens, including ten novels (1836-74)</h3> 
<ul>
	<li><a href="12.html"><span class="book">Sunday under Three Heads</span> (1836)</a></li>	
	<li><a href="pickwick/index.html"><span class="book">Pickwick Papers</span> (35 
	plates, taking over from over Seymour)</a></li>
	<li><a href="sketches/index.html"><span class="book">Sketches of Young 
	Gentlemen</span> (1838) and <span class="book">Sketches of Young Couples</span> 
	(1840)</a></li>	
	<li><a href="nickleby/index.html"><span class="book">Nicholas Nickleby</span> (39 
	plates plus wrapper)</a></li>
	<li><a href="curiosityshop.html"><span class="book">The Old Curiosity Shop</span></a></li>
	<li><a href="../cattermole/mhc.html"><span class="book">Master Humphrey's 
	Clock</span> (with George Cattermole) 11 plates (October 1840)</a></li>
	<li><a href="barnabyrudge/index.html"><span class="book">Barnaby Rudge</span> 
	(with George Cattermole: 61 plates, plus initial-letter vignettes)</a></li>
	<li><a href="mc/index.html"><span class="book">Martin Chuzzlewit</span> (40 
	plates plus sketches)</a></li>
	<li><a href="dombey/index.html"><span class="book">Dombey and Son</span> (40 plates 
	plus sketches)</a></li>
	<li><a href="dc/index.html"><span class="book">David Copperfield</span> (42 plates 
	plus sketches)</a></li>
	<li><a href="bleakhouse/index.html"><span class="book">Bleak House</span></a> (39 
	plates plus sketches)</li>
	<li><a href="ld.html"><span class="book">Little Dorrit</span> (40 plates plus 
	sketches)</a></li>
	<li><a href="85.html">"The Great Wingleberry Duel" in <span class="book">Sketches by 
	Boz</span></a> (1858)</li>	
	<li><a href="2cities/index.html"><span class="book">A Tale of Two Cities</span> (16 
	plates and wrapper plus discussions)</a></li> 
	<li><a href="pphe/index.html"><span class="book">Pickwick Papers</span> (57 plates, 
	in the 1874 Household Edition)</a></li>	
</ul>	
<h3>Works by Charles Lever (1840-63)</h3>
<ul>
	<li><a href="napoleon.html">Phiz and Lever: A Fascination with Napoleon (1840-43; six 
	plates)</a></li>
	<li><a href="lorrequer/index.html"><span class="book">The Confessions of Harry 
	Lorrequer</span></a> (1838)</li>
	<li><a href="omalley/index.html"><span class="book">Charles O'Malley, The Irish 
	Dragoon</span></a> (1840-41; 44 plates)</li>
	<li><a href="hinton/index.html"><span class="book">Jack Hinton, The 
	Guardsman</span></a> (1843; 26 etchings and 9 wood-engravings)</li>
	<li><a href="burke/index.html"><span class="book">Tom Burke of "Ours"</span></a> 
	(1843-44; 44 etchings)</li>
	<li><a href="cashel.html"><span class="book">Roland Cashel</span></a> (1848-1849; 40 
	engravings)</li>
	<li><a href="odonoghue.html"><span class="book">The O'Donoghue; A Tale of Ireland 
	Fifty Years Ago</span></a> (1845; 26 engravings)</li>
	<li><a href="gwynne/index.html"><span class="book">The Knight of Gwynne</span></a> 
	(January 1846 — July 1847; 40 engravings)</li>
	<li><a href="daltons/index.html"><span class="book">The Daltons, or, The Three Roads 
	in Life</span> (1852; 48 plates)</a></li>
</ul>

